 "{{Title: What does XKCD mean?}}
[[One car of two sitting at a red light makes a right turn(COMMA) then shifts over to the left and makes a left turn to go back the way it came. It then makes another right and continues on the road past the traffic light. This is shown with a red arrow.]]
{{Panel title: It means saving a few seconds at a long red light via elaborate and questionably legal maneuvers.}}
[[Someone on a cell phone is shown in a circle in the panel. A second person in the panel itself is looking at a dog(COMMA) from which the ringing sound of his phone is coming]]
<<Ring>>
{{Panel title: It means having someone call your cell phone to figure out where it is.}}
[[The mathematical function "A(g64(COMMA) g64)=(COMMA)" with the 64s subscripted(COMMA) appears in the panel. Next to the equal sign stands a mathematician(COMMA) clutching his head.]]
{{Panel title: It means calling the Ackermann function with Graham's number as the arguments just to horrify mathematicians.}}
Mathematician: Aughhh
[[An approximately 8 by 8 square of floor tiles is shown; the first(COMMA) fourth and seventh across in the first(COMMA) fourth and seventh rows are black and the rest are white. A guy and girl are shown next to it(COMMA) walking on what is presumed to be the same pattern of floor tiles.]]
{{Panel title: It means instinctively constructing rules for which floor tiles it's okay to step on and then walking funny ever after.}}
{{Line indicating the uppermost right black tile: Black tiles okay}}
{{Line indicating tile directly below it: White tiles directly between black tiles okay}}
{{Line indicating a white tile in the last column over: Not okay}}
{{Alt text: It means shuffling quickly past nuns on the street with ketchup in your palms(COMMA) pretending you're hiding stigmata.}}"

